revision.text:
[[ja:鳥取神]] People with mimi in their names include {{Interlanguage link|Suga no Yatsumimi|draft||ja||zh}}, {{ill|Futimi no Kami|ja|布帝耳神}}, {{Ill|Torimimi|ja|鳥取神}}, {{ill|Tahiriki Shimarumi no Kami|ja|多比理岐志麻流美神}}, who appear in the Izumo myth of the [[Kojiki]]. {{ill|Amenohibara Oshinomi no Kami|ja|天日腹大科度美神}} is also considered a regional chief
== See Also ==
* {{nihongo|{{ill|Mimi and Mi|lt=Mimi|ja|ミミおよびミ|draft}}|ミミ、耳、彌彌、美美}}

[[ja:鳥取神]]
Torimimi was a wife of [[Ōkuninushi|Okuninushi]] and a member of the [[User:Immanuelle/17 spirits of the world]]



